<text top="72" left="209" width="198" height="15" font="0"><b>Order of the President of the </b></text>
<text top="94" left="175" width="265" height="15" font="0"><b>Inter-American Court of Human Rights </b></text>
<text top="116" left="242" width="133" height="15" font="0"><b>of August 21, 2007 </b></text>
<text top="138" left="161" width="294" height="15" font="0"><b>Provisional Measures regarding Guatemala </b></text>
<text top="159" left="306" width="8" height="15" font="0"><b>  </b></text>
<text top="181" left="144" width="328" height="15" font="0"><b>Matter of the Forensic Anthropology Foundation </b></text>
<text top="203" left="90" width="4" height="13" font="1"><i><b> </b></i></text>
<text top="217" left="90" width="4" height="13" font="2"><b> </b></text>
<text top="230" left="90" width="4" height="13" font="2"><b> </b></text>
<text top="243" left="90" width="50" height="13" font="2"><b>HAVING</b></text>
<text top="245" left="140" width="3" height="11" font="3"><b> </b></text>
<text top="243" left="143" width="40" height="13" font="2"><b>SEEN: </b></text>
<text top="257" left="90" width="4" height="13" font="2"><b> </b></text>
<text top="270" left="90" width="16" height="12" font="4">1. </text>
<text top="270" left="126" width="401" height="12" font="4">The Order of the Inter-American Court of Human Rights (hereinafter “the </text>
<text top="282" left="90" width="438" height="12" font="4">Court”, “the Inter-American Court” or “the Tribunal”) issued on July 4, 2006, </text>
<text top="294" left="90" width="435" height="12" font="4">whereby it ordered the adoption of provisional measures in favor of members of the </text>
<text top="306" left="90" width="436" height="12" font="4">Forensic Anthropology Foundation (hereinafter, “the FAFG”), among whom was Mr. </text>
<text top="319" left="90" width="171" height="12" font="4">Fernando Arturo López-Antillón.   </text>
<text top="331" left="90" width="3" height="12" font="5"><b> </b></text>
<text top="343" left="90" width="18" height="12" font="4">2.  </text>
<text top="343" left="126" width="401" height="12" font="4">The communication of August 2, 2007, whereby Mr. Fernando Arturo López- </text>
<text top="355" left="90" width="437" height="12" font="4">Antillón requested the Inter-American Court to rescind the measures adopted in his </text>
<text top="367" left="90" width="436" height="12" font="4">favor as a member of the FAFG team, due to the fact that as from July 11, 2007, he </text>
<text top="379" left="90" width="238" height="12" font="4">was no longer working for said organization.    </text>
<text top="392" left="90" width="4" height="12" font="4"> </text>
<text top="404" left="90" width="14" height="12" font="4">3. </text>
<text top="404" left="126" width="401" height="12" font="4">The note of August 10, 2007, whereby the Secretariat of the Inter-American </text>
<text top="416" left="90" width="436" height="12" font="4">Court requested the Inter-American Commission on Human Rights (hereinafter, “the </text>
<text top="428" left="90" width="436" height="12" font="4">Commission” or “the Inter-American Commission”) to submit such observations as it </text>
<text top="440" left="90" width="436" height="12" font="4">might deem pertinent regarding the request to rescind provisional measures filed by </text>
<text top="452" left="90" width="184" height="12" font="4">Mr. Fernando Arturo López-Antillón. </text>
<text top="465" left="90" width="4" height="12" font="4"> </text>
<text top="477" left="90" width="15" height="12" font="4">4. </text>
<text top="477" left="126" width="401" height="12" font="4">The communication of August 14, 2007, whereby the Commission expressed </text>
<text top="489" left="90" width="438" height="12" font="4">that it had no observations to make regarding the request to rescind provisional </text>
<text top="501" left="90" width="436" height="12" font="4">measures adopted in favor of Mr. Fernando Arturo López-Antillón due to the fact that </text>
<text top="513" left="90" width="188" height="12" font="4">he had ceased to work for the FAFG. </text>
<text top="525" left="90" width="4" height="13" font="6"> </text>
<text top="539" left="90" width="4" height="13" font="6"> </text>
<text top="552" left="90" width="89" height="12" font="5"><b>CONSIDERING:</b> </text>
<text top="564" left="90" width="4" height="12" font="4"> </text>
<text top="576" left="90" width="17" height="12" font="4">1. </text>
<text top="576" left="126" width="403" height="12" font="4">That Guatemala has been a State Party to the American Convention on </text>
<text top="588" left="90" width="437" height="12" font="4">Human Rights since May 25, 1978, and accepted the contentious jurisdiction of the </text>
<text top="601" left="90" width="127" height="12" font="4">Court on March 9, 1987. </text>
<text top="613" left="90" width="4" height="12" font="4"> </text>
<text top="625" left="90" width="15" height="12" font="4">2. </text>
<text top="625" left="126" width="401" height="12" font="4">That Article 63(2) of the American Convention establishes that in “cases of </text>
<text top="637" left="90" width="437" height="12" font="4">extreme gravity and urgency, and when necessary to avoid irreparable damage to </text>
<text top="649" left="90" width="437" height="12" font="4">persons,” at the request of the Commission, the Court may adopt such provisional </text>
<text top="661" left="90" width="418" height="12" font="4">measures as it deems pertinent, in matters not yet submitted to its consideration. </text>
<text top="674" left="90" width="4" height="12" font="4"> </text>
<text top="686" left="90" width="18" height="12" font="4">3.  </text>
<text top="686" left="126" width="400" height="12" font="4">That the Inter-American Court ordered, at the request of the Inter-American </text>
<text top="698" left="90" width="437" height="12" font="4">Commission, the adoption of provisional measures in favor of FAFG members and </text>
</page>
