<text top="36" left="90" width="3" height="13" font="7"> </text>
<text top="36" left="303" width="6" height="13" font="7">2</text>
<text top="72" left="90" width="437" height="12" font="4">other persons, among whom was Mr. Fernando Arturo López-Antillón (<i>supra</i> Having </text>
<text top="84" left="90" width="112" height="12" font="4">seen paragraph 1).   </text>
<text top="96" left="90" width="4" height="12" font="4"> </text>
<text top="108" left="90" width="18" height="12" font="4">4. </text>
<text top="108" left="126" width="404" height="12" font="4">That Mr. Fernando Arturo López-Antillón requested that the provisional </text>
<text top="121" left="90" width="436" height="12" font="4">measures adopted in his favor be rescinded, since he was no longer working for the </text>
<text top="133" left="90" width="208" height="12" font="4">FAFG  (<i>supra</i> Having seen paragraph 2). </text>
<text top="145" left="90" width="4" height="12" font="4"> </text>
<text top="157" left="90" width="15" height="12" font="4">5. </text>
<text top="157" left="126" width="401" height="12" font="4">That the Inter-American Commission did not submit any observations to the </text>
<text top="169" left="90" width="438" height="12" font="4">request to rescind provisional measures adopted in favor of Mr. Fernando Arturo </text>
<text top="181" left="90" width="250" height="12" font="4">López-Antillón (<i>supra</i> Having seen paragraph 4). </text>
<text top="194" left="90" width="4" height="12" font="4"> </text>
<text top="206" left="90" width="14" height="12" font="4">6. </text>
<text top="206" left="126" width="400" height="12" font="4">That the Court deemed it necessary to adopt provisional measures in favor of </text>
<text top="218" left="90" width="438" height="12" font="4">FAFG members in view of the threats they have received in relation to the work </text>
<text top="230" left="90" width="438" height="12" font="4">performed by the Foundation concerning the identification and recovery of human </text>
<text top="242" left="90" width="436" height="12" font="4">remains. Due to the fact that Mr. Fernando Arturo López-Antillón’s work relationship </text>
<text top="254" left="90" width="437" height="12" font="4">with the FAFG has ceased to exist, and in light of the request filed directly by said </text>
<text top="266" left="90" width="441" height="12" font="4">beneficiary, this President deems it unnecessary to maintain the provisional </text>
<text top="279" left="90" width="252" height="12" font="4">measures ordered in his favor by the Tribunal.     </text>
<text top="291" left="90" width="4" height="13" font="6"> </text>
<text top="304" left="90" width="4" height="13" font="6"> </text>
<text top="317" left="90" width="74" height="12" font="5"><b>THEREFORE: </b></text>
<text top="330" left="90" width="3" height="12" font="5"><b> </b></text>
<text top="342" left="90" width="399" height="12" font="5"><b>THE PRESIDENT OF THE INTER-AMERICAN COURT OF HUMAN RIGHTS, </b></text>
<text top="354" left="90" width="4" height="12" font="4"> </text>
<text top="366" left="90" width="439" height="12" font="4">in exercise of the authority conferred on him by Article 63(2) of the American </text>
<text top="378" left="90" width="436" height="12" font="4">Convention on Human Rights and Article 25 of the Court’s Rules of Procedure, and in </text>
<text top="390" left="90" width="382" height="12" font="4">consultation with the Judges of the Inter-American Court of Human Rights,<b> </b></text>
<text top="403" left="90" width="4" height="12" font="4"> </text>
<text top="415" left="90" width="4" height="12" font="4"> </text>
<text top="427" left="90" width="58" height="12" font="5"><b>DECIDES: </b></text>
<text top="442" left="90" width="3" height="11" font="9"> </text>
<text top="453" left="90" width="19" height="12" font="4">1.  </text>
<text top="453" left="126" width="402" height="12" font="4">To rescind the provisional measures adopted pursuant to the Order of the </text>
<text top="465" left="90" width="438" height="12" font="4">Inter-American Court of Human Rights of July 4, 2006 in favor of Mr. Fernando </text>
<text top="477" left="90" width="117" height="12" font="4">Arturo López-Antillón.  </text>
<text top="489" left="90" width="4" height="12" font="4"> </text>
<text top="501" left="90" width="15" height="12" font="4">2. </text>
<text top="501" left="126" width="401" height="12" font="4">To request the Secretariat of the Inter-American Court of Human Rights to </text>
<text top="514" left="90" width="437" height="12" font="4">give notice of this Order to the Inter-American Commission on Human Rights, the </text>
<text top="526" left="90" width="335" height="12" font="4">representatives of the beneficiaries and the State of Guatemala.   </text>
<text top="538" left="90" width="7" height="12" font="4">  </text>
<text top="550" left="90" width="4" height="12" font="4"> </text>
<text top="562" left="90" width="4" height="12" font="4"> </text>
<text top="574" left="90" width="4" height="12" font="4"> </text>
<text top="586" left="90" width="4" height="12" font="4"> </text>
